	<td>
	  Self-organizing Agile teams are a hallmark of Agile software development. How Agile teams are meant to self-organize in practice, however, is not well understood. Based on an original, industry-based PhD research involving 58 Agile practitioners from 23 software organizations, this tutorial provides an overview of self-organizing teams from multiple perspectives and a description of the roles on Agile teams that make them self-organizing. This presentation will include practical implications and tips to help software practitioners better understand their roles and responsibilities in establishing and sustaining self-organizing Agile teams.
